{
  "texts": [
    "The operator ∆ represents the variation of a phasor with respect to its pre-fault value, while the superscript \"pre\" indicates pre-fault conditions.",
    "The subscript loop designates the loop quantities defined in Table 1.",
    "Finally, d is the estimated fault distance, d max is the line length, and Z 1 is the positive-sequence line impedance, where Re(Z 1) and Im(Z 1) denote its real and imaginary parts.",
    "Feature SelectionThe construction of a suitable feature set required a systematic selection process to identify variables that provide high predictive value while avoid- ing redundancy.",
    "To this end, two complementary techniques were applied:Mutual Information (MI) [17] and Pearson correlation analysis.First, MI was employed to quantify the statistical dependence between each candidate feature and the target variable, defined as the correction factor for fault location."
  ]
}